npc/bayu: You've made it through. Adbots, Bandits, the Witch's collectors — all of them.
npc/bayu: But those were just the outer layer. Foot soldiers sent from somewhere deeper.
npc/bayu: Every one of those creatures is being projected here through a signal — from inside the internet itself.
npc/bayu: The gate ahead leads into Stage 2: the threshold between this world and the digital one.
npc/bayu: Someone left a gambling app open in this city. The signal is still live — and it's pulling things through.
npc/bayu: You have to go in. Follow the signal. Trace it back through the network to wherever it originates.
npc/bayu: At the end of it all, there is something they call the House. The Algorithm. The Core that every other part of this answers to.
npc/bayu: Every soul this city lost — every person hollowed out by debt and despair — their suffering feeds it.
npc/bayu: The Adbots and Bandits you fought today? They used to be people, just like you.
npc/bayu: It believes one thing above all else: the house always wins.
npc/bayu: It has never been wrong. Until now.
npc/bayu: Go. And whatever you do — don't play its game.
